:: Rejection target: a single conditional cluster whose consequent contains
:: both `solid` and `non solid` is statically contradictory. Deriving an
:: attribute and its negation for the same subject signals an unsound
:: registration and must be rejected before it can enter the active cluster
:: database (doc/spec/en/17.clusters_and_registrations.md, sections 17.4 and
:: 17.7.3; architecture 04 lists contradictory attributes as a registration
:: diagnostic).

definition
  let x be set;
  attr HollowDef: x is hollow means x = x;
  attr SolidDef: x is solid means x = x;
end;

registration
  cluster HollowContradiction: hollow -> solid non solid for set;
  coherence proof thus thesis; end;
end;
